'''Alexander Prass''' (born 26 May 2001) is an Austrian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] or [[left wing-back]] for {{German football updater|Hoffenhe}} club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|alexander-prass/508728}}</ref>

==Club career==
Born in [[Hellmonsödt]], [[Upper Austria]], Prass began his career as a youth player at [[LASK]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fohler |first1=Gernot |title=Alex ist roter Bulle |url=https://www.meinbezirk.at/urfahr-umgebung/c-sport/alex-ist-roter-bulle_a234473 |access-date=21 November 2023 |work=MeinBezirk.at |date=8 August 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231121180726/https://www.meinbezirk.at/urfahr-umgebung/c-sport/alex-ist-roter-bulle_a234473 |archive-date=21 November 2023 |language=de}}</ref> Between 2009 and 2010 he played at FC Pasching before returning to LASK. For the 2012–13 season he moved to the youth team of [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]], where he would later also play in the academy.

In March 2019 he was named for the first time in the matchday squad of Salzburg feeder team [[FC Liefering]] for a game against [[SK Vorwärts Steyr]], but did not come on. He made his debut for Liefering in the second flight in the same month when he came on as an 87th minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Karim Adeyemi]] against [[FK Austria Wien II|Austria Wien II]]. In two and a half years with Liefering, he made a total of 59 second division appearances, in which he scored twelve goals.

For the 2021–22 season he moved to [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Ö Bundesliga]] club [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]], where he received a contract until June 2024, extending this for a year in July 2022 to keep him at the club until the end of the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]]|url=https://www.sksturm.at/de/news/kampfmannschaft/2021/alexander-prass-unterschreibt-bei-sturm/|title=ALEXANDER PRASS UNTERSCHREIBT BEI STURM|date=28 May 2021|language=de|access-date=10 September 2021|archive-date=12 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220112040937/https://www.sksturm.at/de/news/kampfmannschaft/2021/alexander-prass-unterschreibt-bei-sturm/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 5 August 2024, Prass signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] on a long-term contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/aktuelles/news/2024/08/tsg-verpflichtet-oesterreichischen-nationalspieler-alexander-prass|trans-title=TSG signs Austrian international Alexander Prass|title=TSG verpflichtet österreichischen Nationalspieler Alexander Prass|language=German|website=www.tsg-hoffenheim.de|date=5 August 2024|accessdate=5 August 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Prass made his [[Austria national under-18 football team|Austrian U-18]] debut on 9 October 2018 against [[Switzerland national under-18 football team|Switzerland's U-18]] squad. Just two days later, he scored his first goal for an Austrian squad, this time against Switzerland. In October 2019, he made his debut for the [[Austria national under-19 football team|Austrian U-19]] squad in a match against Wales U-19. By March 2021, he had made his debut for the [[Austria national under-21 football team|Austrian U-21]] squad against [[Saudi Arabia national under-20 football team|Saudi Arabia]].

In November 2022, the winger received his first call-up to the senior Austrian national team.<ref>[https://www.oefb.at/oefb/News/Nationalteam-Kader-fuer-die-Spiele-gegen-Andorra-und-Italien-nominiert National team squad for the matches against Andorra and Italy nominated] oefb.at, November 8, 2022, retrieved November 8, 2022.</ref> He made his senior debut later that month in a match against the [[Andorra national football team|Andorra national team]]. In May 2024, he was named in Austria's preliminary squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024|2024 European Championship]]<ref>[https://www.oefb.at/oefb/News/Grosskader-UEFA-EURO-2024 Rangnick nominates large squad for UEFA EURO 2024] oefb.at, May 21, 2024, retrieved June 4, 2024</ref> and was eventually included in the final squad.<ref>[https://www.oefb.at/oefb/News/OeFB-Kader-UEFA-EURO-2024 National team squad for UEFA EURO 2024 confirmed] oefb.at, June 7, 2024, retrieved June 8, 2024</ref> Austria was eliminated in the round of 16, losing 1-2 to the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]], but Prass appeared in all four of Austria's matches during the tournament.{{Commons category|Alexander Prass}}

